parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The unavailability of parts for the Takata airbag recall can lead to a delay in the repair, putting the driver and passengers at risk of fatal injury or death in the event of an accident.
symptoms: as the issue is related to the unavailability of parts for the recall repair.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Takata Airbag Recall - Lack of Communication
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The lack of communication from the manufacturer and dealerships can lead to frustration and anxiety for the vehicle owners, who are left uncertain about the status of the recall repair.
symptoms: as the issue is related to the lack of communication.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The inadequate solution offered by the manufacturer, such as not allowing anyone to ride in the front passenger seat, can be inconvenient and unacceptable for vehicle owners.
symptoms: as the issue is related to the inadequate solution.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the electrical wiring harness can cause exterior lights to malfunction or fail, leading to reduced visibility and increased risk of accidents. In severe cases, it can also cause fires in the engine compartment.
symptoms: wires exposed due to brittle or cracked insulation
fire hazard in the engine compartment.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Intermittent headlight failure can cause reduced visibility, increasing the risk of accidents, especially at night or in low-light conditions.
TCM failure can cause the vehicle to shift erratically or not shift into gear, leading to loss of control and increased risk of accidents.
symptoms: Vehicle does not shift into gear on startup

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Sudden fuel shut-off and deceleration can cause loss of control, increasing the risk of accidents, especially at high speeds.
symptoms: loss of power transfer during acceleration.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Central Computer and Electrical System Failure
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Failure of the central computer and electrical system can cause the vehicle to shut down suddenly, leading to loss of control and increased risk of accidents.

The failure of the headlights can significantly reduce visibility while driving at night, increasing the risk of accidents. Flickering headlights can also cause distractions and impair the driver's ability to react to road conditions.
symptoms: Headlights turn off or flicker while driving
especially at night; dipped headlight warning or error code displayed; rear lights warning of bulbs out at random times; shutting lights off and on resolves the issue temporarily.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake lights can reduce the visibility of the vehicle to other drivers, increasing the risk of rear-end collisions. Melting of the brake light assembly can also cause a fire hazard.
symptoms: Brake lights flicker or fail to function; smoke enters the cabin; brake light assembly melts; rear lights warning of bulbs out at random times.
